description: The team learn how the kids from Neverland survived the zombie apocalypseâ€”and what happened to all of the adults. When the grim revelations are finished, Planters and Fulton decide to do something nice for the children, but their actions may lead to disaster for everyone.

Winning a baking contest has never been more challenging! Not when Jughead is involved, that is! Will Betty and Veronica come out on top with a prize winning cake or will Jughead's insatiable appetite doom them from the start? The answer lies in the hilarious conclusion to "The Mark of Jughead!"
name: The Mark of Jughead

description: Jughead as Captain Hero in "The Collector" â€“ Veronica is taken captive by The Collector, an evil-doer with a penchant for dark haired go-go girls! Not even the super powered combination of Pureheart and Evilheart can stop the dastardly villain! Will Jughead's super alter ego Captain Hero manage to save the say or will his enormous appetite be his ultimate downfall? Discover the answer in this nail biting adventure plus many more!
name: The Collector

description:
World War Two is over, but Airboy's work isn't done! Davy Nelson, the teenaged fighting ace known to the world as Airboy, returns to the skies in this brand new limited series!

Using his miraculous plane, Birdy, Davy finds and defeats a Japanese air ace holding out on a remote island. When he visits the man in postwar Tokyo, Airboy uncovers a conspiracy that could plunge Japan into the maelstrom of war once again!

The final battle! STORM SHADOW leads his ninja on an attack that threatens to cripple Americaâ€™s national security! The only men who can stop him are SNAKE EYES and ROADBLOCKâ€”but can they put aside their differences and learn from each other in time? Itâ€™s ninja and commando action in the frantic G.I. JOE manner, leading ino the hottest movie of 2012!

Featuring an explosive cover by series storyteller Steve Conley and comics legend STERANKO (Nick Fury, Agent of S.H.I.E.L.D., The Shadow), this first plutonium-powered issue introduces the retro-universe of Argosy Smith, Theremin and a cosmos of new characters. Beginning part one of "The Codex Reckoning" the characters seek the Codex Melzi - mysterious lost notes of Leonardo da Vinci. As a backup story, a 7-page retro sci-fi adventure "The Victor Belt" features the Hero of Strata 4, Jet Victor by Marty Baumann. As an extra bonus: a sci-fi pin-up from STERANKO!

The third comic of the original run was released in January 1999.In the feature story, "Aspects of Iron": Argosy Smith is dead, so what is he doing running from dinosaurs, robots and the Velthan mystic who prophesized his death? And while Argosy is galavanting in the afterlife, his cohorts are no better off! Petra's being chased by a Bounty Hunter and Theremin's up to his globules in Musketeers. This issue also features a Jet Victor episode by Marty Baumann. PLUS: a sci-fi pin-up by comics legend Pat Boyette!

The Age of Aquarius: 1968. It's the end of illusions for the Archons as the world sinks into disenchantment. Dyo intervenes to suppress the Prague Spring, sending his best man, Kim Philby. Curtis sees his chance, and aims to finally wreak some vengeance. At the other end of the Earth, Erlin discovers in the ruins of a Mayan temple strange correspondence from his old friend, Nostradamus. What if the Archons had never really understood the meaning of their destiny?
name: Book Nineteen: The Age of Aquarius

description: Collects : West Coast Avengers (1985) #25 - New Mutants (1983) #52

The End of Camelot. California, 1960: The millionaire Howard Hughes convenes a meeting of the Cosa Nostra to offer them a contract on President John F. Kennedy. At the other end of the earth, Curtis is on the trail of John Philby, the murderer of his wife, hunting him in Saudi Arabia, intent on ending him once and for all but the game changes constantly!
name: Book Eighteen: The End of Camelot

name: Titans

description: Despite Kuro and Manaâ€™s best efforts, the two high mototsumitama are no match for Shion, one of Reishin Shishigamiâ€™s top generals. Amused by Manaâ€™s arrogance, Shion reveals that the proud purebloods are actually an impure breed descended from the original mototsumitama, who gave up the purity of their race in order to survive. Without the powerful battle genes of her ancestors, Kuro cannot hope to defeat Shion, let alone Reishin. Filled with rage, Kuro launches a ferocious attack unlike anything the others have ever seen. Has Kuro unlocked some hidden power of her own, or will this sudden surge of bloodlust take her out of commission for good?!
name: Vol. 16

description:
Full Metal Panic: Overload! is not so much a sequel to the first manga series as it is a retelling of the FMP mythos. Originally serialized in a magazine aimed at slightly younger readers, Overload! has the same basic story with a lot more comedy and a lot more explosions!

Sosuke has finally lost his mind - and his memory! Rehashing his previous exploits will keep Kaname busy, but it doesn't take long for the military mind of this soldier to bounce back with a bang - literally! He's locked, loaded, and back to his old self by first period, as bombs and bullets grace the halls of high school!
name: Volume 1

description: When Sosuke's old military rival worms his way into the halls of Jindai High and into the hearts of the female students, it's all-out war on the toughest battlefield of them all... the classroom! Sosuke will set his studies aside to dish out a few lessons in the art of combat, but another invasion interrupts his assignment. He'll have to ward off the evil that threatens Kaname with the most lethal weapon he can find - cold medicine!
name: Volume 2

description: As an agent of Mithril, Sosuke Sagara has seen more than his share of the battlefield, but now he will have to face the most formidable enemy of all - the workplace! From restaurants to video rental shops, Sosuke throws himself headlong into the fray, but it's going to take some serious firepower to make it through this nine-to-five skirmish!
name: Volume 3

description: Sousuke has finally lost his mind, and it's up to Kaname to keep him in line! So what's new? Plenty! Check out this laugh-out-loud sequel to one of ADV's best-loved manga series. Featuring more bombs, more laughs and more Panic than ever before!
name: Volume 4

description: Turrets, barbed wire, and... teddy bears? Jindai High is under lockdown, and it's no mystery who the culprit is. But once Sosuke starts filling the classrooms with gun-toting teddy bears, everyone starts to wonder if he's finally flipped out! There's more to these teddies that meets the eye, though, and there's more to Sosuke than he's letting on - his mission to protect Chidori is over and he's been ordered back to base! And just to make sure he complies, a familiar face shows up with a teddy-bear army of his own, leading to a battle that could bring the school down! The mayhem concludes in this explosive final volume!
name: Volume 5

description: Angelic Days takes the angst-ridden EVA pilots of Neon Genesis Evangelion and sets them in the lighter, brighter world of high school. Harried, harassed, and harangued - that's Shinji Ikari's life in a nutshell. Still, his days are fairly typical for a Tokyo teenager: he's got a pushy pal in Asuka who rudely rouses him whenever he's running late for school, and he's surrounded by the standard assortment of high school goofballs. In fact, everything's just as you'd expect, until one day when Shinji bumps into a strange girl he's never seen before, and she promptly accuses him of peeking up her skirt! But that's not the worst of it. Strange dreams have been haunting his sleep lately-dreams of a robotic "other" just beyond the horizon. With comedy, action, and romance (plus a fair share of fan service), Angelic Days is the manga NGE fans have been waiting for!
name: Volume 1

description: An impromptu outing causes the students of class 2-A to learn the truth - that they are being groomed as pilots of enormous artificial beings called Evangelion. Before the day is through, two of these students will have to don their plugsuits and use the Evangelion in the first of many battle to come. But that's nothing compared to the angst in the air as Asuka and Rei grapple with their feelings for Shinji. Can these hormone-addled teens put aside the affairs of the heart long enough to save their city?
name: Volume 2

description: Designed for military use, the Steel Angel is a fearsome android warrior. But she's designed to obey the person who activates her. When a young boy inadvertently does so, he finds himself with an adoring - and adorable - new companion, and quite a headache. You see, the military wants Kurumi back, and definitely doesn't plan to go quietly...
name: Volume 1

description: Steel Angel Kurumi, created by a brilliant scientist, was supposed to have used her super-human strength on behalf of the military. However, Kurumi cannot be activated by her makers, and she lies in the machine equivalent of a coma. Nakahito, the son of practitioners of the magical technique called "Onmyo Way," stumbles upon the inert goddess, and struck by her amazing beauty, gently kisses her perfect lips. With this kiss, the Steel Angel Kurumi comes to life, and Nakahito becomes her master. The gorgeous and voluptuous Kurumi will now do anything to protect her master with her invincible power. But first, critical questions about Kurumi's origins must be answered: "Why and where was Kurumi created? Who created her?" Nakahito and Kurumi set out on a dangerous search to find the answers to these questions and, along their journey, they are forced to ask an additional question: "Who is behind the insidious activation of other Steel Angels whose only mission is to destroy the beautiful Steel Angel Kurumi?"
name: Volume 2

description: Kurumi and her friends try their luck at being idol singers. "Discovered" and "trained" by a mysterious mummy man wearing a suit (Mikhail), they rise to fame with the release of their first record. Unfortunately, their fame only makes them a threat to two envious, established stars, who want to see the "Steel Angel Trio" out of the picture. As the Steel Fight competition nears the end of its first stage, Kurumi, Saki, and Karinka (who are all unaware that the competition is going on) learn that Kaga and two other angels of destruction are impersonating them, using their advanced powers to destroy the normal Steel Angels, snatch their emblems, and give Kurumi the "points." His cover ultimately blown, Kaga reveals that Dr. Ayanokoji is at the Academy, but that the Steel Angel Trio will have to compete in that final round to learn anything more. Finally, a strange girl is scared off during Kurumi's date with Nakahito, a girl, who - in an unexpected turn of events - is revealed to readers (but not the steel angels) as none other than... Shinobu Jinguji!
name: Volume 4

description: When young Nakhito placed a single, innocent kiss on the lips of a sleeping girls, he got much more than he expected - the Steel Angel Kurumi, a lovely and very devoted robot companion who just happens to be a lethal warrior as well. Fists fly as Kurumi continues to engage in devastating conflict with other Steel Angels and those who would control her!
name: Volume 5

description: Nakahito travels 100 years into the future to seek a cure for the spell that has been cast on him. With his Steel Angel companion, Kurumi, along with Karinka and Saki, they discover a future world largely governed by an order of Steel Angels(and their masters) that protect humanity from natural disasters and duel one another to settle international disputes. World peace has been achieved and science has progressed significantly. When a future mystic-Amato kanui-challenges Nakahito to a duel, Kurumi must fight Amato's Steel Angel, Excelia, who has the advantages of 100 years of future technological firepower!
name: Volume 6

description: The Steel Angels are still enduring an altered future and have managed to make a few enemies along the way. What appears to be a hopeless defense against the more-advanced Steel Angel Excelia soon turns to Kurumi's favor, when she uses "love power" to transform into an Angel. But it is uncertain whether or not her newfound power will be strong enough to fight off her master's new love interest. Apparently, time hasn't healed the wounds of unrequited love, as an extremely mature Ms. Jinguji lays a predatory stake on a very young, very frightened Nakahito. The Angels may have the strength to take down other robots, but a woman scorned - this will take an army!
name: Volume 7

description:
The angelic androids stir-up the future again with their antics, but instead of raising their fists they pull-out their...recipes! Kurumi and her sisters have been challenged to a test of culinary prowess by the newest Steel Angel, Seira, subordinate to her master, the "Grand Cook." The girls may spice it up in the kitchen, but Kurumi and company must tend to poor Nakahito, weakened by a taxing spell cast upon his young body. It's up to his adoring and oh-so-cute Steel Angel to save him, but when fierce, flying demons threaten to ruin the day, will Kurumi be up to the task?

Contents

  • Episode 41: The Apron of Love
  • Episode 42: The Third Angel of Angels
  • Episode 43: Graduation Day (Part 1)
  • Episode 44: Graduation Day (Part 2)
  • Episode 45: Graduation Day (Part 3)
  • Episode 46: End of the Century
  • Bonus Story: Daydreaming Angel Saki
  • Afterword: Bonus Comic
name: Volume 8

description: Sugar and spice make everything... trouble for the Steel Angels! A flashback reminds the Steel Angels of a distressing vulnerability, making them appear even more human. Kaga ponders the growth of Nakahito's mystical abilities, while a more powerful Aoi plans to bolster her reputation in a Steel Fight rematch. In the meantime, the ridiculously cute Kurumi, Saki and Karinka continue their quest to rid their dear, sweet Nakahito of the deadly curse cast against him. But, when the trouble mounts, and an enigmatic and powerful mystic enters the scene, Kurumi gets an idea that may save the day... besides, Kurumi needs attention, and without her master, there's not telling what she will do!
name: Volume 9

description:
Living the low life

It takes a special kind of judge to go undercover on the mean streets of Mega-City One - especially in the crime infested Low Life; the nastiest part of the 'Big Meg'. This division of the Justice Department known as the 'Wally Squad' contains some of the bravest individuals working the streets â€“ and also some of the most unhinged!

Join Judges Aimee Nixon, Thora, 'baby Judge' Mortal and Dirty Frank as they encounter some of the biggest threats ever to appear in the Low Life, including a new reality-altering drug called 'Creation' and a war on the streets between the Justice department and the Yakuza!

THIS VOLUME INCLUDES THE FOLLOWING STORIES:

War without Bloodshed (Judge Dredd Megazine #271-274)

Creation (2000 AD #1624-1631)

Jive Turkey (2000 AD Prog 2010)

Hostile Takeover (2000 AD #1700-1709)

ANYTHING GOES IN SIN CITY!

The largest mobile man-made structure the world has ever known has come to the shores of Mega-City One and people are flocking to the island with sin on their mind. However, hiding amongst the dens of iniquity and vice is international terrorist Ula Danser, waiting to release a storm of devastation on the citizens of the Big-Meg.

It's a race against time as Dredd and his team try to find Danser before all hell breaks loose!

Written by Dredd's co-creator John Wagner (A History of Violence) with art by Kev Walker (The Eternal) this high-octane adventure is just too tempting to miss!

THIS VOLUME INCLUDES THE STORIES

Sin City (progs 1289-1299)

Case for the Defence (prog 1303)

The Trial Of Orlok (progs 1336-1337)

Plus!

Covers gallery

Author Biographies

Note: Thopugh the lead story is called Sin City, the collection was called Satan's Island to avoid infringing on the trademark of Frank Miller's Sin City series.

TOTAL CARNAGE!

In the Grand Hall of Justice a chilling ultimatum is issued to the Judges: Remove yourselves from power or face the consequences. Somewhere in Mega-City One the terrorist organisation Total War have planted two hundred thermonuclear devices and as long as the Judges stay in charge they will detonate them one by one.

Total War is an explosive epic from Judge Dredd co-creator John Wagner (A History of Violence) with art from Colin MacNeil (Devlin Waugh), Henry Flint (Judge Dredd Vs Aliens) and Jason Brashill (Shaun of the Dead).

THIS VOLUME CONTAINS THE STORIES

Terror (progs 1392-1399)

Total War (progs 1408-1419)

After the Bombs (progs 1420-1422)

Plus!

Author Biographies

THE RED RIGHT HAND OF JUSTICE!

There is a new wave of dissent in Mega-City One. Politicians are calling for an end to summary justice only to be silenced by a new and deadly force. However, this is no renegade: this is The Justice Killer, a deadly puppet whose strings lead back to the very heart of the Grand Hall of Justice itself!

Penned by Judge Dredd co-creator John Wagner (A History of Violence) with art from Will Simpson (Hellblazer), John Burns (Nikolai Dante) and Colin MacNeil (Devlin Waugh) this tale of violent conspiracy is Judge Dredd at its thrilling best!

THIS VOLUME CONTAINS THE STORIES

The Chief Judges Man (progs 1244-1247)

On the Chief Judges Service (progs 1263-1266)

Revenge of the Chief Judges Man (progs 1342-1349)

Plus!

John Wagner's original script

Covers gallery

Author Biographies

volume.name: Judge Dredd: The Chief Judge's Man

description: Superman gets trapped in a virtual reality version of Metropolis and has to fight his way back to the real world.
name: Dimension of the Dark Shadows

volume.name: Batman: Antes de la Hora Cero

description: The Rasta Man teams up with the Voodoo Queen to put in play a plan to rid New Orleans of the human vengeance squad who feel that they have the moral blessing to win the war.
name: Origins - Part 2

description:
Crossfire and Rainbow take down a cadre of would-be assassins when Rainbow's psychic hologram powers go berserk. Things go from bad to worse when she starts broadcasting her illusions through the psychic link she shares with the other DNAgents. It's a race against time to save a visiting dignitary while the Maitrix Corporation's research team tries to figure out who sabotaged Rainbow's powers.

*This issue also contains a four page cover gallery of DNAgents and Crossfire covers, all presented in 3D.
name: Deep Dreams

description: Bob Fingerman's Beg the Question tells the story of Rob and Sylvia, two twenty-somethings navigating the labyrinth of New York City life. Imagine a cross between Seinfeld and Caligula, set in Manhattan, and you'll have an idea of Fingerman's caustic wit. Beg the Question follows Rob & Sylvia's relationship through all of its ups-and-downs, from courtship to marriage, rentals to real estate salesmen, public sex to unwanted pregnancies, and everything in between. Performance art, extended families, the comic book industry and Screw magazine are just a few of the other topics subjected to Fingerman's satirical microscope. Fingerman's mid-1990s comic book series Minimum Wage was a breakthrough success, and this marks the first collection of the entire run, completely retouched, with added gray tones that give the art a much fuller, richer look, plus almost 40 pages of never-before-published material. Find out why Beg the Question is one of the most critically acclaimed graphic novels we've ever published!
